The Papers of the British School at Rome'' 86 (2018): 1-24.\n*Wiseman, T.P.  \"The Lupercalia.\" In ''Remus: A Roman Myth''. Cambridge, Cambridge University Press, 1995, pp.&nbsp;77\u201388, limited preview [https://books.google.com/books?id=7LPNHRUlWacC&printsec=frontcover&dq=lupercal+OR+lupercalia&lr=&as_brr=3&as_pt=ALLTYPES&source=gbs_summary_r&cad=0#PPA77,M1 online], discussion of the Lupercalia in the context of myth and ritual.\n* Wiseman, T.P. \"The God of the Lupercal,\" in Idem, ''Unwritten Rome''. Exeter, University of Exeter Press, 2008.\n*Gardner, Constance \"[https://www.meridiangraphics.net/lupercalia/ Lupercalia]\"\n\n==External links==\n*[http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/secondary/SMIGRA*/Lupercalia.html William Smith, ''Dictionary of Greek and Roman Antiquities,'' 1875]: Lupercalia\n\n{{Roman religion (festival)}}\n{{Roman religion}}\n\n[[Category:Ancient Roman festivals]]\n[[Category:February observances]]\n[[Category:Wolves in folklore, religion and mythology]]\n[[Category:She-wolf (Roman mythology)]]\n", "name_user": "Smjg", "label": "safe", "comment": "MOS:LQ", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lupercalia"}
{"title_page": "PDS5B", "text_new": "{{Infobox_gene}}\n'''Sister chromatid cohesion protein PDS5 homolog B''' '''(PDS5B)''' is a [[protein]] that in humans is encoded by the ''PDS5B'' [[gene]].<ref name=\"pmid8812419\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Couch FJ, Rommens JM, Neuhausen SL, Belanger C, Dumont M, Abel K, Bell R, Berry S, Bogden R, Cannon-Albright L, Farid L, Frye C, Hattier T, Janecki T, Jiang P, Kehrer R, Leblanc JF, McArthur-Morrison J, Meney D, Miki Y, Peng Y, Samson C, Schroeder M, Snyder SC, Simard J | title = Generation of an integrated transcription map of the BRCA2 region on chromosome 13q12-q13 | journal = Genomics | volume = 36 | issue = 1 | pages = 86\u201399 |date=Feb 1997 | pmid = 8812419 | pmc =  | doi =10.1006/geno.1996.0428  |display-authors=etal}}</ref><ref name=\"pmid10215036\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Geck P, Szelei J, Jimenez J, Sonnenschein C, Soto AM | title = Early gene expression during androgen-induced inhibition of proliferation of prostate cancer cells: a new suppressor candidate on chromosome 13, in the BRCA2-Rb1 locus | journal = J Steroid Biochem Mol Biol | volume = 68 | issue = 1\u20132 | pages = 41\u201350 |date=May 1999 | pmid = 10215036 | pmc =  | doi =10.1016/S0960-0760(98)00165-4  }}</ref><ref name=\"entrez\">{{cite web | title = Entrez Gene: APRIN androgen-induced proliferation inhibitor| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=gene&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=23047| accessdate = }}</ref> It is a regulatory subunit of the [[Cohesin]] complex which mediates [[Establishment of sister chromatid cohesion|sister chromatid cohesion]], homologous recombination and [[Topologically associating domain|DNA looping]]. The core cohesin complex is formed of SMC3, [[SMC1A|SMC1]], [[RAD21]] and either [[STAG1|SA1]] or [[STAG2|SA2]]. PDS5 associates with [[WAPL|WAPAL]] to stimulate the release of cohesin from DNA but during DNA replication PDS5 promotes acetylation of SMC3 by [[ESCO1]] and [[ESCO2]].\n\n==Model organisms==\n{| 